	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Gamers.com reviews Velious</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=324292" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <P>
Gamers.com has posted a <a href="http://www.gamers.com/ec/pc/284581/reviews/index">new review</A> of the Scars of Velious. It seems like their reviewer is stuck in the past here, and he basically reviews the old game instead of sticking to what's new with the expansion pack. It's an acceptable overview, but seems a little biased to me as whoever reviewed this obviously doesn't care for EQ too much, and the main people that are attracted to an expansion pack are existing customers... They should have found someone else to write up this review, so in other words you can probably skip this article. Here's a snip none the less.
<Blockquote>
Another very noticeable refinement lies in the updated graphical user interface (UI) which features a transparent inventory, allowing you to view your character's possessions without having to switch screens. The maximum playable resolution has also been bumped up from 1024x800 to 1600x1200, so those of you with large monitors can take advantage. The rest of us are happy with the ability to move and resize on-screen windows (chat windows, spell-casting, health bars, etc.); the customizable UI is an extremely neat feature and a godsend for those players who like to personalize their screen. The expansion, available for $10 to $20 dollars, is almost worth buying just for the improved UI alone. 
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=324292">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
